<br>
Yup---the Internet was a mere shadow of its current self, and if you were off-campus, you were just plain out of luck for surfing (unless you used Lynx from a Unix prompt---a daunting, text-only experience).<br>
<br>
As such, the best place to find neato files and such were on the local BBSes. I remember uploading a Won by One press pack to one of 'em (that band's now called Wallace Green, by the way).<br>
<br>
